Driver badly injured in accident
In an accident on Thursday evening, a 37-year-old car driver has been seriously injured in Aachen.
According to the police was a 41-year-old from Müsch against 21.15 with her car in the Kempener Außenring towards Gref Rath.
When the wanted to turn left onto the St. Töniser street, they overlooked the oncoming car of the 37-year-olds.
The Fahrzauge collided.
The Aachen suffered serious injuries and had to be brought for treatment in the hospital.
